WEBVTT

00:07.960 --> 00:08.910
Are you embarrassed
to be with me?

00:09.100 --> 00:10.490
I've just worked
too fucking hard

00:10.690 --> 00:12.740
to be forever be known as
"The Girlfriend" in The Six.

00:12.940 --> 00:14.660
- Do you understand that?
- Yeah, actually, I do.

00:14.860 --> 00:16.220
Are you sure you're okay?

00:17.390 --> 00:19.540
<i>[Camila] There were just</i>
<i>so many secrets.</i>

00:19.740 --> 00:20.920
You kept the one line
that didn't work.

00:21.120 --> 00:22.170
It was just the rest
that was shit.

00:22.370 --> 00:24.590
- [whistles]
- It's not what you think, man.

00:24.790 --> 00:26.210
I could've sworn
you two were together.

00:26.410 --> 00:27.470
How do you know we're not?

00:27.660 --> 00:28.840
Not according to Billy.

00:29.040 --> 00:30.800
He said it's
all about the music.

00:31.000 --> 00:32.760
And, uh, what was the name
of that recovery clinic?

00:32.960 --> 00:35.010
- Who told you about that?
- You're a rock star,
what're you gonna do?

00:35.210 --> 00:37.390
I mean, they don't all miss
their daughter's christening.

00:37.590 --> 00:39.020
- How could you tell him?
- You said it was
all about the music.

00:39.220 --> 00:40.480
<i>- This is about the music.</i>
<i>- That's why you kissed me?</i>

00:40.680 --> 00:42.110
<i>So I'd get back on the mic?</i>

00:42.300 --> 00:43.360
I'd say it was worth it,
wouldn't you?

00:43.560 --> 00:44.670
You're a fucking liar.

00:46.000 --> 00:47.320
Don't put my daughter
in your story.

00:47.520 --> 00:49.090
Give me something better then.

00:53.260 --> 00:56.290
Simone, Bernie,
this is Nicky Fitzpatrick.

00:56.490 --> 00:57.290
The rings, please.

00:57.490 --> 00:58.660
[Petros speaks in Greek]

00:58.860 --> 01:00.210
[bells ringing]

01:00.410 --> 01:01.460
[Nicky] Maybe she's right.

01:01.660 --> 01:03.210
Maybe you should go back.

01:03.410 --> 01:06.600
[Nicky] I won't let anyone
hurt you ever again.

01:08.230 --> 01:09.940
[♪ Patti Smith:
"Dancing Barefoot"]

01:11.860 --> 01:14.100
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

01:14.290 --> 01:16.180
♪ <i>Is benediction</i> ♪

01:16.380 --> 01:18.350
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

01:18.550 --> 01:20.390
♪ <i>Is addicted to thee</i> ♪

01:20.590 --> 01:22.560
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

01:22.760 --> 01:24.650
♪ <i>Is the root connection</i> ♪

01:24.850 --> 01:26.770
♪ <i>She</i> ♪

01:26.970 --> 01:28.860
♪ <i>Is connecting with he</i> ♪

01:29.060 --> 01:31.030
♪ <i>Here I go</i> ♪

01:31.230 --> 01:32.990
♪ <i>And I don't know why</i> ♪

01:33.190 --> 01:37.700
♪ <i>I fell so ceaselessly</i> ♪

01:37.900 --> 01:40.710
♪ <i>Could it be he's taking</i> ♪

01:40.900 --> 01:42.350
♪ <i>Over me</i> ♪

01:45.980 --> 01:50.260
♪ <i>I'm dancing barefoot</i> ♪

01:50.460 --> 01:54.260
♪ <i>Heading for a spin</i> ♪

01:54.460 --> 01:55.760
♪ <i>Some strange music</i> ♪

01:55.960 --> 01:58.810
♪ <i>Draws me in</i> ♪

01:59.010 --> 02:00.310
♪ <i>Makes me come on</i> ♪

02:00.510 --> 02:03.040
♪ <i>Like some heroine</i> ♪♪

02:13.420 --> 02:15.030
<i>[Camila gasps] Look, Jules,</i>
<i>it's Daddy.</i>

02:15.230 --> 02:16.280
<i>[Julia and Billy laughing]</i>

02:16.480 --> 02:17.840
<i>That's so exciting.</i>

02:18.880 --> 02:21.750
<i>"Coming to a city near you</i>
<i>this winter."</i>

02:21.950 --> 02:23.710
Except it wasn't true.

02:23.910 --> 02:26.920
I mean, there was still
no trace of her anywhere.

02:27.120 --> 02:29.590
Didn't show up for mixing,
rehearsals...

02:29.790 --> 02:31.510
Well, some of us
couldn't help but wonder

02:31.710 --> 02:33.300
if she was gone for good.

02:33.500 --> 02:36.340
And I think one of us was...

02:36.540 --> 02:38.050
probably hoping for that.

02:38.250 --> 02:40.200
[laughter and chattering]

02:55.920 --> 02:57.740
I was just trying to hold
this thing together.

02:57.940 --> 02:58.990
<i>Let's run through "Aurora"</i>

02:59.190 --> 03:00.990
with that intro
we were kicking around.

03:01.190 --> 03:04.210
So you want to start the set
with "Aurora"?

03:04.400 --> 03:07.520
That's what we decided, yeah.

03:08.560 --> 03:09.540
Interesting.

03:09.740 --> 03:11.050
Warren, when you're ready.

03:11.240 --> 03:13.090
- One...
- And these are the songs

03:13.290 --> 03:14.300
that you want to sing?

03:14.500 --> 03:15.380
That's right.

03:15.580 --> 03:17.800
No "Regret Me"?
No "Look at Us Now"?

03:18.000 --> 03:20.350
Well, if you wanted to weigh in,
the time for that was weeks ago,

03:20.550 --> 03:21.910
when we first started rehearing.

03:24.120 --> 03:25.390
Do you guys need a minute?

03:25.590 --> 03:27.140
No. Warren, count us in.

03:27.340 --> 03:29.000
Yes, actually, we do.

03:34.590 --> 03:35.820
What the hell is your problem?

03:36.020 --> 03:36.820
You called me "icing."

03:37.020 --> 03:38.610
You said I was a "head case"

03:38.810 --> 03:40.280
to <i>Rolling Stone</i> magazine.

03:40.480 --> 03:41.530
You told a journalist

03:41.730 --> 03:43.200
about me missing the birth
of my daughter.

03:43.400 --> 03:45.450
- So what?
- I told you that
in confidence, Daisy,

03:45.650 --> 03:47.210
because I trusted you.

03:47.410 --> 03:49.380
Don't act like you didn't
fucking do anything.

03:49.570 --> 03:50.500
- What does that mean?
- "Talent like Daisy's

03:50.700 --> 03:52.210
is wasted on somebody
like Daisy."

03:52.410 --> 03:54.130
That's what you said.

03:54.330 --> 03:55.630
You made me look weak.

03:55.830 --> 03:58.130
You made me look
like I need you.

03:58.330 --> 04:00.240
So we both told the truth then.

04:01.240 --> 04:02.560
[sighs]

04:02.750 --> 04:04.310
[door closes]

04:04.510 --> 04:06.850
[guitar and drums
play simple tune]

04:07.050 --> 04:08.390
It's gonna be a long tour,

04:08.590 --> 04:10.270
so if you'd prefer to sit this
one out, please be my guest.

04:10.470 --> 04:13.070
There's no tour without me,
you dumb son of a bitch.

04:13.270 --> 04:14.580
We're playing "Regret Me."

04:16.040 --> 04:17.950
- Fine.
- And "Look at Us Now."

04:18.150 --> 04:18.990
- No.
- Yes.

04:19.190 --> 04:20.170
I said no, Daisy.

04:21.840 --> 04:24.330
Warren, count us in,
for the love of fucking God.

04:24.530 --> 04:26.410
What'd I miss?

04:26.610 --> 04:29.350
[♪ The Sweet:
"The Ballroom Blitz"]

04:30.390 --> 04:31.330
Who the fuck is this guy?

04:31.530 --> 04:33.390
Everybody, this is Nicky.

04:34.690 --> 04:36.310
My husband.

04:38.020 --> 04:39.630
Hi.

04:39.830 --> 04:40.640
- [♪ The Sweet:
"The Ballroom Blitz"]
<i>- [Mick] Okay.</i>

04:40.830 --> 04:43.430
<i>[Brian] All right, fellas.</i>

04:43.630 --> 04:45.770
<i>Let's go...!</i>

04:45.960 --> 04:47.910
♪ ♪

04:51.910 --> 04:54.070
It's just more practical
with the costume changes.

04:54.260 --> 04:55.730
Or you could wear less costumes.

04:55.930 --> 04:58.320
A private dressing room
isn't that much to ask for.

04:58.520 --> 04:59.860
Then I want a separate
green room.

05:00.060 --> 05:01.860
- For what?
- For those of us
who aren't gonna use

05:02.060 --> 05:04.030
before every show, Daisy.

05:04.230 --> 05:06.800
That's you. So you want a
private green room just for you.

05:09.260 --> 05:10.920
<i>[Rod] Managing The Six</i>
<i>had somehow become</i>

05:11.110 --> 05:12.330
<i>the hottest gig in town.</i>

05:12.530 --> 05:14.710
Billy never forgot what
I'd done for him back in '71

05:14.910 --> 05:17.270
so when he called me up...

05:18.310 --> 05:20.300
...I jumped at the chance.

05:20.500 --> 05:21.760
I don't know if you heard,
but I'm married now,

05:21.960 --> 05:23.300
so I'd like a suite
for all these overnights.

05:23.500 --> 05:25.010
Well, I'm married, too.

05:25.210 --> 05:26.390
But your wife's
not coming on tour.

05:26.590 --> 05:27.680
Not the whole time
but I'm sorry,

05:27.880 --> 05:28.850
if she gets a suite,
I get a suite, too.

05:29.050 --> 05:30.990
- On a separate floor.
- Oh, even better.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.270
Why not get separate buses
while you're at it?

05:34.470 --> 05:36.170
- Is that possible?
- Can we do that?

05:38.830 --> 05:41.740
Seemed like a good idea
at the time.

05:41.940 --> 05:43.200
You have one album.

05:43.400 --> 05:45.780
This is the kinda shit
you can ask for

05:45.980 --> 05:48.870
when you're Crosby, Stills
& Nash, okay?

05:49.070 --> 05:52.960
There's no way the label's
gonna sign off on any of this.

05:53.160 --> 05:55.130
[chuckles]

05:55.330 --> 05:57.500
They said yes to everything.

05:57.700 --> 05:59.650
[♪ The Sweet:
"The Ballroom Blitz"]

06:02.270 --> 06:04.280
[speaking indistinctly]

06:06.820 --> 06:08.180
Oh, take care of yourself. Mwah.

06:08.380 --> 06:09.680
- I'm gonna miss you so much.
- I'm gonna miss you.

06:09.880 --> 06:11.560
- Mwah.
- Bye.

06:11.760 --> 06:13.480
[Karen] Bye.

06:13.680 --> 06:15.120
[Rod] Got it.

06:17.000 --> 06:18.320
[Billy] Put it in
the driver bay.

06:18.520 --> 06:20.460
[speaking Spanish]

06:24.250 --> 06:25.510
Be safe.

06:26.510 --> 06:27.990
[man] You're first one on,
last one out.

06:28.190 --> 06:30.580
Put the talent up front.

06:30.780 --> 06:33.290
[Graham] Okay,
take care of your mom, okay?

06:33.490 --> 06:36.670
- Oh, Julia gets
so many Graham hugs.
- Oh, I'll miss you so, so much.

06:36.870 --> 06:38.290
- Hey.
- Huh? Can I get a Graham hug?

06:38.490 --> 06:39.550
Mm.

06:39.740 --> 06:40.960
Take care of him, okay?

06:41.160 --> 06:42.210
- See you soon.
- Okay.
- [Billy grunts]

06:42.410 --> 06:43.800
Gonna miss me?

06:44.000 --> 06:46.240
Oh. Say goodbye.

06:46.740 --> 06:48.220
You sure you don't want to come?

06:48.420 --> 06:51.390
Oh, yeah, it'd be so fun
with a two-and-a-half year old.

06:51.590 --> 06:53.310
- I'm gonna miss you
- Gonna miss you.

06:53.510 --> 06:54.990
[Rod] Billy.

06:57.790 --> 06:59.230
Hey, man.

06:59.430 --> 07:00.610
Come on, get this show
on the road.

07:00.810 --> 07:03.030
- All right, all right.
- Okay.

07:03.230 --> 07:04.460
Go be a rock star.

07:05.500 --> 07:07.300
All right.

07:11.340 --> 07:13.350
[bus pulling away]

07:16.140 --> 07:18.830
Night one was in Albuquerque.

07:19.030 --> 07:20.750
See, you-you don't start
in New York or L.A.

07:20.950 --> 07:24.090
where the crowd is nothing
but critics and suits.

07:24.290 --> 07:26.970
You want to start small,
off-market,

07:27.170 --> 07:28.970
where you can get your sea legs
under you,

07:29.170 --> 07:30.890
work out the kinks.

07:31.090 --> 07:32.140
- [microphone feedback]
- ♪ <i>Boy, it would kill you</i> ♪

07:32.340 --> 07:36.940
♪ <i>To try...</i> ♪

07:37.140 --> 07:38.560
Can you do that phrase again,
Daisy.

07:38.760 --> 07:39.650
I'm getting some feedback.

07:39.850 --> 07:41.320
Maybe stop moving around
so much.

07:41.510 --> 07:44.990
I mean, the mic gets shaky
with you flittering around.

07:45.190 --> 07:46.400
So let's fix it.

07:46.600 --> 07:47.660
Well, how are they supposed
to light you

07:47.850 --> 07:49.370
if you can't stand still?

07:49.560 --> 07:51.280
Hey! Excuse me!

07:51.480 --> 07:54.160
Can you light me
if I'm moving around?

07:54.360 --> 07:56.410
Uh, I mean,
yeah, whatever you guys want.

07:56.610 --> 07:57.830
Wonderful.

07:58.030 --> 07:59.890
Let's run through the song.

08:01.060 --> 08:02.520
Yeah, sure.

08:03.560 --> 08:05.380
<i>[Karen] If I'm being honest,</i>

08:05.580 --> 08:08.050
we were pretty sure Albuquerque
would be a disaster.

08:08.250 --> 08:10.530
[♪ "The River"]

08:12.030 --> 08:14.640
<i>But it was fantastic.</i>

08:14.840 --> 08:17.020
♪ <i>If I follow you to the river</i> ♪

08:17.220 --> 08:18.940
♪ <i>If I follow you</i>
<i>to the river</i> ♪

08:19.140 --> 08:22.440
♪ <i>And the shadow crawling</i>
<i>towards you</i> ♪

08:22.640 --> 08:24.580
[guitar riff]

08:26.130 --> 08:28.200
♪ <i>Oh...</i> ♪

08:28.400 --> 08:30.780
- ♪ <i>I'd follow you</i>
<i>to the river</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>I want you there</i> ♪

08:30.980 --> 08:32.490
♪ <i>In the shadow</i> ♪

08:32.690 --> 08:34.200
♪ <i>In the river</i> ♪

08:34.400 --> 08:38.540
♪ <i>Your affection is a promise</i>
<i>you couldn't keep</i> ♪

08:38.740 --> 08:41.630
♪ <i>I know, I know, I know,</i>
<i>I know, I know, oh</i> ♪

08:41.830 --> 08:47.010
- ♪ <i>Oh, if I follow you</i>
<i>to the river</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>Oh...</i> ♪

08:47.210 --> 08:50.690
- ♪ <i>If I follow you there</i> ♪
- ♪ <i>To the river</i> ♪♪

08:57.240 --> 08:58.770
We had to work together.

08:58.970 --> 09:01.650
We didn't have
to like each other.

09:01.850 --> 09:03.190
And we didn't.

09:03.390 --> 09:05.820
Thank you, Albuquerque!

09:06.020 --> 09:07.670
[whistling and cheering]

09:09.040 --> 09:10.500
[squeals happily]

09:13.130 --> 09:15.330
[Nicky] That was incredible.

09:15.530 --> 09:18.450
[cheering continues]

09:18.650 --> 09:20.600
[phone ringing]

09:27.190 --> 09:28.380
[softly] Hello.

09:28.580 --> 09:30.470
How's my little girl?
She miss me?

09:30.670 --> 09:31.840
<i>Billy, it's been like</i>

09:32.040 --> 09:33.390
two days.

09:33.590 --> 09:35.260
<i>Can you put her on?</i>

09:35.460 --> 09:36.600
[inhales deeply]

09:36.800 --> 09:39.270
Um... it's the middle
of the night.

09:39.470 --> 09:41.690
<i>She's been asleep for hours.</i>

09:41.890 --> 09:45.000
Here, you can listen
to her dream, okay?

09:48.380 --> 09:51.200
Hey, baby.

09:51.390 --> 09:53.130
It's Daddy.

09:55.920 --> 09:57.240
<i>[Camila] Okay, well,</i>
<i>I'm gonna go back to bed.</i>

09:57.440 --> 09:58.870
<i>I'll call you tomorrow.</i>

09:59.070 --> 10:00.890
<i>I love you.</i>

10:01.890 --> 10:03.520
♪ ♪

10:15.990 --> 10:18.700
[music continues distantly]

10:24.200 --> 10:26.200
[party chatter
and music continue]

10:28.330 --> 10:31.030
This time is gonna be different.

10:31.230 --> 10:33.610
<i>- This is Billy Dunne.</i>
<i>- And I'm Daisy Jones.</i>

10:33.810 --> 10:37.280
And you're listening
to KAKC AM 970 radio Tulsa.

10:37.480 --> 10:39.580
KBOX Dallas.

10:39.780 --> 10:41.410
"The rock of Fort Worth."

10:41.610 --> 10:43.970
KFJZ.

10:46.680 --> 10:48.960
That was great, Mike. Thank you.

10:49.160 --> 10:50.500
[Mike] Thank you all.
Appreciate it.

10:50.700 --> 10:52.170
Thanks for having us.

10:52.370 --> 10:55.180
[cheering loudly]

10:55.380 --> 10:56.840
[♪ Boston:
"More Than a Feeling"]

10:57.040 --> 10:58.640
Oh, my God.

10:58.840 --> 11:01.560
Tributes to the Temple
of Daisy Jones.

11:01.760 --> 11:05.310
♪ <i>I looked out this morning</i>
<i>and the sun was gone...</i>

11:05.510 --> 11:06.560
By Christmas,
they had the number three song

11:06.760 --> 11:07.770
in the country

11:07.970 --> 11:10.650
and the number nine song
in the country.

11:10.850 --> 11:13.900
<i>We booked them on</i> Bandstand,
Midnight Special.

11:14.100 --> 11:15.490
<i>There were rumors</i>
<i>about</i> Saturday Night Live.

11:15.690 --> 11:16.780
<i>All the shows were selling out,</i>

11:16.980 --> 11:19.370
<i>new dates being added</i>
<i>all the time.</i>

11:19.570 --> 11:21.370
[♪ Boston:
"More Than a Feeling"]

11:21.570 --> 11:23.510
[crowd cheering]

11:24.640 --> 11:26.500
All right, take it easy.

11:26.700 --> 11:27.790
Don't make me bring out
the big guns.

11:27.990 --> 11:30.170
♪ ♪

11:30.370 --> 11:31.630
Hi.

11:31.830 --> 11:32.880
What?

11:33.080 --> 11:34.970
[crowd screaming excitedly]

11:35.170 --> 11:36.880
♪ <i>It's more than a feeling</i> ♪

11:37.080 --> 11:39.680
♪ <i>More than a feeling</i> ♪

11:39.880 --> 11:41.970
It was every band's
dream come true.

11:42.170 --> 11:44.180
♪ <i>More than a feeling</i> ♪

11:44.380 --> 11:45.810
- ♪ <i>I begin dreaming</i> ♪
- Eddie, come on,
get out of here.

11:46.010 --> 11:48.400
♪ <i>More than a feeling</i> ♪

11:48.600 --> 11:50.610
♪ <i>Till I see Marianne</i>
<i>walk away</i> ♪

11:50.810 --> 11:53.690
- Hey. All right.
- [screaming excitedly]

11:53.890 --> 11:55.900
- ♪ <i>I see my Marianne</i> ♪
- Hey.

11:56.100 --> 12:01.550
♪ <i>Walkin' away...</i>

12:06.560 --> 12:08.080
[Teddy] Where are we going, Don?

12:08.280 --> 12:10.580
Something I want you to see.

12:10.780 --> 12:13.130
Zero to 60
in under five seconds.

12:13.330 --> 12:15.630
Top speed about 165.

12:15.830 --> 12:17.130
You know who else
drives one of these?

12:17.330 --> 12:18.800
007 himself.

12:19.000 --> 12:19.970
Pretty nice car.

12:20.170 --> 12:21.430
You like it?

12:21.630 --> 12:23.100
What's not to like?

12:23.300 --> 12:25.490
Good, 'cause she's yours.

12:27.330 --> 12:29.980
We've had some hits before,
you and I,

12:30.180 --> 12:31.860
but these numbers, Teddy...

12:32.060 --> 12:33.270
The phone's been ringing
off the hook.

12:33.470 --> 12:34.730
Big names, too.

12:34.930 --> 12:37.360
You know, heroes of mine.
Some of 'em.

12:37.560 --> 12:39.410
What's it gonna take
for you to stay in house?

12:39.600 --> 12:40.990
[scoffs]

12:41.190 --> 12:44.030
Well, a lot more
than a Ferrari 308.

12:44.230 --> 12:46.120
But you already knew that...

12:46.320 --> 12:47.500
didn't you?

12:47.700 --> 12:50.040
[chuckles quietly]

12:50.240 --> 12:51.960
Here. Don't drive her too fast--

12:52.160 --> 12:53.980
we got work to do.

12:55.520 --> 12:57.380
[♪ "Kill You to Try"]

12:57.580 --> 13:00.590
<i>[Daisy]</i> ♪ <i>Show me,</i>
<i>I'd blind myself to see it</i> ♪

13:00.790 --> 13:03.680
♪ <i>What is it?</i>
<i>What is it I must do?</i> ♪

13:03.880 --> 13:07.470
♪ <i>If I tell you,</i>
<i>promise me you'll mean it</i> ♪

13:07.670 --> 13:09.890
♪ <i>Let me come,</i>
<i>let me come home to you</i> ♪

13:10.090 --> 13:13.940
♪ <i>Show me,</i>
<i>I'd blind myself to see it</i> ♪

13:14.140 --> 13:17.320
♪ <i>What is it?</i>
<i>What is it I must do?</i> ♪

13:17.520 --> 13:20.740
♪ <i>If I tell you,</i>
<i>promise me you'll mean it</i> ♪

13:20.940 --> 13:24.070
♪ <i>Let me come,</i>
<i>let me come home to you</i> ♪

13:24.270 --> 13:27.200
♪ <i>Show me,</i>
<i>I'd blind myself to see it</i> ♪

